name: three and five layered board production | three and five layered board | Cutoff, U
description:
ecoQuery: https://ecoquery.ecoinvent.org/3.10/cutoff/dataset/23852/documentation

This dataset represents the global production of three-layered and 5-layered laminated board. it was created as copy of the corresponding local datset for Europe. This is a special form of plywood featuring relatively thick layers.;Data are based on a German production sample.;The three-layered/five-layered laminated board are made from logwood: out of rough sawn timber (u=70%) 22 mm lamellas are sawn, which are technically dried, planed, finger-jointed, glued with PVAc-adhesive at their ends to “never-ending” lamellas and finally glued to a bloc. This block is sawn to boards, which are planed.;Reference:;Rüter, S. and S. Diederichs (2012): Ökobilanz-Basisdaten für Bauprodukte aus Holz. Arbeitsbericht aus dem Institut für Holztechnologie und Holzbiologie Nr. 2012/1, Johann Heinrich von Thünen-Institut (vTI), Hamburg. ;[This dataset is meant to replace the following datasets:; - three layered laminated board production, GLO, 1997 - 2002 (1aa7aaae-cc76-4bde-90b1-886aaebbbf92)]

From the reception at the factory gate of all materials and fuels used.

This activity ends with the three layered/five layerd board produced at the factory gate. The dataset includes the inputs to and outputs of the production processes and the available process emissions. Infrastructure is a rough estimate.

processDocumentation.geographyDescription: Data for Germany used for central Europe
processDocumentation.technologyDescription: Technology reflects a sample of German plywood production. The three-layered or 5-layered laminated board is actually a special form of plywood featuring relatively thick layers.
processDocumentation.samplingDescription: Literature; emissions profile per MJ wood input from PSI (2014)

exchanges.description:
Reference product. Plywood produced in Germany by processes representative for European average. The reference product is ready for delivery at the wooden board factory. 
A large number of materials can be produced with differing properties and areas of use. Typical uses are as construction plywood for wall, floor, and ceiling panels and also as panels for concrete shuttering, and decorative covering veneers in interior furnishings (e.g. wall panels or doors).
